foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: The number of requests pending at the start of the fiscal year is 32 lower for FAA, 3 lower for FHWA, 11 lower for FMCSA, and 1 lower for NHTSA, than reported at the end of last year's report. The adjustments reflect requests where all final action was taken in FY 2014, but the close-outs were not captured in the tracking system in FY 2014. For this reason, the overall agency number of requests pending at the start of the fiscal year is 47 lower than reported in last year's report.

foia:OtherDenialReason.foia:OtherDenialReasonDescriptionText: RITA became part of OST during the FY; all RITA cases were absorbed by OST and reflected in OST's numbers

foia:ProcessedAppealSection.foia:FootnoteText: The number of pending appeals for the agency overall at the beginning of Fiscal Year 2015 is the same as that reported as pending at the end of the Fiscal Year 2014. However, the number is 2 higher for FAA, 1 lower for FMCSA, and 1 lower for OST than reported in last year's report. In FAA, two appeals were received in FY 2014, but not logged in until FY 2015. Both FMCSA and OST completed action on an appeal in FY 2014, but did not log it out until FY 2015.
